HEADWORD: Orthotomic
<hw>Or`tho*tom"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ortho-</ets> + Gr. <?/ to cleave.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>
<def>Cutting at right angles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Orthotomic circle</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>that
circle which cuts three given circles at right angles.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orthotomous</ent>⟦br⟧
